  "total_points": 9,
  "stimulus": "The Maclaurin series for a function $f$ is given by $\\sum_{n=1}^{\\infty} \\dfrac{(-1)^{n+1}}{n \\cdot 2^n} x^n = \\dfrac{x}{2} - \\dfrac{x^2}{8} + \\dfrac{x^3}{24} - \\dfrac{x^4}{64} + \\cdots + \\dfrac{(-1)^{n+1}}{n \\cdot 2^n} x^n + \\cdots$ and converges to $f(x)$ for $|x| < R$, where $R$ is the radius of convergence of the Maclaurin series.",
  "stimulus_image": null,
  "documents": null,
  "parts": [
    {
      "letter": "a",
      "prompt": "Use the ratio test to find $R$, the radius of convergence of the Maclaurin series for $f$.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": null,
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "a1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct ratio test setup: $\\lim_{n \\to \\infty} \\left|\\dfrac{a_{n+1}}{a_n}\\right| = \\lim_{n \\to \\infty} \\left|\\dfrac{x^{n+1}}{(n+1) \\cdot 2^{n+1}} \\cdot \\dfrac{n \\cdot 2^n}{x^n}\\right|$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$\\lim_{n \\to \\infty} \\left|\\dfrac{n \\cdot x}{2(n+1)}\\right|$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct simplification of the limit: $\\lim_{n \\to \\infty} \\dfrac{n}{n+1} \\cdot \\dfrac{|x|}{2} = \\dfrac{|x|}{2}$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$\\dfrac{|x|}{2} < 1$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct conclusion: series converges when $\\dfrac{|x|}{2} < 1$, i.e., $|x| < 2$, so $R = 2$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$R = 2$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
